-- India Cooking-Oil Imports Seen at Record as Harvests Drop
-- B y   P r a t i k   P a r i j a
-- 2012-03-19T12:06:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-19/india-cooking-oil-imports-seen-at-record-as-harvests-drop.html
Oilseed production in  India , the
world’s largest palm oil importer, may climb 2.3 percent this
year on bigger harvests of soybeans and peanuts, the Central
Organization for Oil Industry and Trade said.  Production may increase to 26.02 million metric tons in the
2011-2012 crop season from 25.44 million tons a year earlier,
B.V. Mehta, joint convener of the organization’s crop committee,
said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Pratik Parija in  New Delhi  at 
 pparija@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 James Poole  at   jpoole4@bloomberg.net . 